Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.39,0:00:17.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Archer, I don't believe it. You—
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.68,0:00:21.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You once asked me this, Saber:
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.60,0:00:25.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,"Have you no pride as a hero?"
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.23,0:00:29.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Of course I haven't.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.96,0:00:34.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,All I have left is foolish regrets.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.32,0:00:37.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The thing is, Saber...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.79,0:00:42.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I should never have become a hero.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.79,0:00:48.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I suggest you stand aside, King of Knights.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.05,0:00:52.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If you exert yourself with no Master, \Nyou will quickly disappear.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.47,0:00:57.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Emiya Shirou is no longer qualified to be a Master.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.82,0:01:01.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Aiding him will not help your wish come true.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.81,0:01:09.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I swore that I would protect him, \Nthat I would be his sword.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.11,0:01:14.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Even without our pact, that pledge \Nremains unchanged.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.89,0:01:15.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.70,0:01:19.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,In that case...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.44,0:02:53.44,Title,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(273,1)}#18  The Beginning of the Circle
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.19,0:03:19.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Disappear here, you and your false master.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.83,0:03:28.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I expected you to cower a bit longer.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.35,0:03:29.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.83,0:03:31.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You're fighting the wrong person!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.46,0:03:38.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,A near enough imitation is, \Neffectively, the real thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.55,0:03:43.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But can your body handle that \Nlevel of magical exertion?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.14,0:03:48.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Using magic beyond your ability will destroy you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.81,0:03:58.09,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Or did you honestly think you would succeed?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.74,0:04:03.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That if you stubbornly kept trying, your ideal \Nself would be within your grasp?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.54,0:04:08.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Archer...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.17,0:04:23.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Emiya Shirou has reached his limit.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.14,0:04:27.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,A fitting end for a fool who constantly \Ntried to do the impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.73,0:04:31.81,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Heed my words.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.85,0:04:36.92,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,My will creates your body, and your \Nsword creates my destiny.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.92,0:04:41.85,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If you heed the Grail's call and \Nobey my will and reason...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.74,0:04:49.76,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Then answer me!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.19,0:04:53.48,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Do so and I will entrust my destiny to your sword!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.08,0:04:57.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,On my honor as a Saber, I accept your oath.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.88,0:05:01.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I accept you as my Master, Rin.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.94,0:05:20.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What will it be, Saber?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.83,0:05:22.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Now that you've made a pact with Rin,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.90,0:05:26.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,it means you truly have no further \Nties to Emiya Shirou.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.22,0:05:29.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Weren't you listening, Archer?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.62,0:05:31.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,My pledge to Shirou stands.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.00,0:05:35.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And what will you do?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.35,0:05:39.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,As I am now, surely you do not \Nthink you can defeat me.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.42,0:05:46.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,How confident you've become, \Nsimply because your mana is restored.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.98,0:06:05.07,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's over, Archer.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.15,0:06:08.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Earlier, you voiced concern for my condition,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.99,0:06:11.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,but now I could say the same to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.87,0:06:14.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You have nothing to anchor you to this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.62,0:06:18.75,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You have nothing to supply you with \Nmana, so what can you do?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.84,0:06:25.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Servants of the Archer class have \Nthe ability to act independently.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.01,0:06:29.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Without a Master, I think I can last two days or so.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.84,0:06:33.49,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,More than enough time to put down that boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.97,0:06:36.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I can't believe it. You're still talking about that?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.39,0:06:39.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Or are you saying your wish \Nwas never the Holy Grail,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.90,0:06:42.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,but killing Shirou?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.11,0:06:48.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Archer, your wish is mistaken.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.41,0:06:52.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Mistaken, is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.45,0:06:55.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You took the words out of my mouth, Saber.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.94,0:06:59.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,How long will you embrace \Nyour own mistaken wish?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.75,0:07:03.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You didn't fail to leave a legacy.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.38,0:07:07.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Can't you think of it as an end \Nto everything you could do?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.56,0:07:17.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I am an Archer.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.32,0:07:19.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I was never meant to fight using swords.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.65,0:07:22.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Admittedly...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.23,0:07:26.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,My bow is just as much a borrowed forgery.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.94,0:07:29.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm saying that I will show you my true nature.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.36,0:07:34.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That is the greatest recompense \Nthat I can offer you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.66,0:07:37.77,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I am the bone of my sword.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.77,0:07:39.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Stop, Archer!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.41,0:07:40.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I do not wish to...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.21,0:07:42.96,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Unknown to Death,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.96,0:07:45.23,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Nor known to Life.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.75,0:07:49.63,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Saber, one day, someone will \Nappear who will free you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.38,0:07:54.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But the sole objective of my current \Nself is to kill Emiya Shirou.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.51,0:08:00.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If you try to prevent that, this world \Nwill not show mercy, even to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.94,0:08:04.25,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Unlimited...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.32,0:08:07.09,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Blade Works.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.07,0:08:24.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,A Reality Marble?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.46,0:08:29.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,A forbidden spell that manifests the caster's \Ninner world and encroaches on reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.32,0:08:34.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Which means that you aren't \Na swordsman or a bowman.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.95,0:08:37.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.24,0:08:42.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,When I was alive, I was a mage \Nbefore I became a Heroic Spirit.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.60,0:08:45.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Then what is your Noble Phantasm, Archer?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.11,0:08:51.07,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I owned neither a holy sword nor a demonic one.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.07,0:08:54.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,All I have is this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.78,0:08:57.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If a Noble Phantasm is a Heroic Spirit's symbol,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.74,0:09:00.75,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,then this Reality Marble is my Noble Phantasm.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.75,0:09:05.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It reproduces and stores any weapon \Nwhose original I've seen.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.63,0:09:09.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That is my ability as a Heroic Spirit.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.88,0:09:10.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Then this...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.55,0:09:16.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You're saying this wasteland is where \Nyou ended up in life, Archer?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.68,0:09:19.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You don't mince words.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.53,0:09:20.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Care to test it, Saber?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.73,0:09:25.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'll faithfully replicate that holy sword of yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.73,0:09:27.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,My holy sword?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.69,0:09:31.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, it's a projection that's certain \Nto end in my destruction,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.69,0:09:33.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,but I can produce a convincing replica.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.32,0:09:36.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It should last long enough to take you with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.32,0:09:40.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,However, when two holy swords clash,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.66,0:09:43.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,will any humans in the vicinity survive?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.04,0:09:45.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That son of a...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.96,0:09:47.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Feel free to dodge them.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.58,0:09:50.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But if you do, you doom the man behind you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.20,0:09:52.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Shirou?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.55,0:09:59.23,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If the rules and principles of all the copying \NI've done so far are right...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.57,0:10:01.37,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Trace...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.48,0:10:04.08,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,on!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.02,0:10:09.33,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Faster.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.63,0:10:11.38,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Better.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.28,0:10:13.36,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Stronger.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.19,0:10:16.89,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I can see how this place works.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.45,0:10:22.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sick of your crap!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.46,0:10:28.75,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Archer, what do you think you're...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.38,0:10:31.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Tohsaka!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.09,0:10:39.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Where are you going, Archer?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.35,0:10:42.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I'm back to square one.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.76,0:10:45.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That gambit depleted my mana.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.36,0:10:48.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Now that you're at 100%, I'm no match for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.77,0:10:51.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This is my insurance policy.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.20,0:10:55.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If you value your Master's life, I suggest \Nyou stay out of this, Saber.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.45,0:10:57.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,My objective is that boy's—
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.74,0:10:59.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The forest outside of town.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.20,0:11:01.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.42,0:11:04.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,There's a castle that's empty now.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.41,0:11:05.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Shirou?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.95,0:11:08.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You want to give me a piece of your mind?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.19,0:11:10.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Fine, let's hear it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.26,0:11:13.25,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,There are things I want to say to you, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.17,0:11:17.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,True, we won't be interrupted at that castle.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.26,0:11:21.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I like your resolve, Emiya Shirou.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.14,0:11:22.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Go to hell.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.47,0:11:24.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I dare you to hurt Tohsaka.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.14,0:11:25.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'll kill you!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.22,0:11:28.75,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I guarantee her safety for one day.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.19,0:11:30.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Be quick, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.81,0:11:34.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Without a Master, I won't last for two days.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.61,0:11:37.25,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If I haven't managed to kill you by that time,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.78,0:11:40.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I might just dismember my hostage out of spite.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.16,0:11:45.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Shirou!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.74,0:11:47.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You're being reckless.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.06,0:11:51.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Not even you can perform the same \Nprojections as Archer so quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.90,0:11:54.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, Saber.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.38,0:11:56.67,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I let Tohsaka get captured.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.34,0:12:00.63,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Right now, you are in more danger than she is.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.63,0:12:02.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Let me worry about Rin.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.64,0:12:05.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You should return home and rest.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.44,0:12:19.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like you took care of business, kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.24,0:12:22.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's not like that, Saber.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.34,0:12:25.25,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,He helped us.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.33,0:12:29.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Are you saying that Lancer assisted you, Shirou?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.58,0:12:31.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, he did.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.64,0:12:34.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So for now, try not to fight him, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.58,0:12:36.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Why, Lancer?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.71,0:12:41.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Do you have some ulterior motive \Nin helping Shirou and Rin?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.55,0:12:44.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Of course I have an ulterior motive.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.01,0:12:47.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Like I'd help them if I didn't \Nexpect something out of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.68,0:12:50.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.11,0:12:52.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Meaning that you've gotten what you wanted.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.31,0:12:53.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Then begone.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.60,0:12:55.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I won't fight you now, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.05,0:13:01.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, it appears things didn't go \Nentirely according to plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.54,0:13:04.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What happened in there, kid?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.78,0:13:08.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Tohsaka's been abducted by Archer.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.75,0:13:15.14,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This hill is his world.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.14,0:13:18.75,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It was his reward for always helping people,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.75,0:13:20.42,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,the end of the line.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.26,0:13:24.36,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It seemed like he'd embraced this landscape,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.36,0:13:27.32,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,dying with a smile, saying he was satisfied.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.12,0:13:30.09,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Seriously? How stupid is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.61,0:13:35.16,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, that made me really angry.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.06,0:13:37.81,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,He worked and worked,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.81,0:13:40.19,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,striving for greatness, even though he was ordinary,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.19,0:13:43.17,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,finally achieving his miracle as he bled.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.90,0:13:46.87,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So he has to be happy, or all of that will be a lie.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.41,0:13:49.83,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If he made lots of people happy,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.83,0:13:55.83,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,he should become at least as happy \Nas those people combined.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.50,0:13:59.96,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,However, that wasn't the reward he received.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.30,0:14:01.69,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Instead, all he got
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.44,0:14:06.85,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,was being exploited as a Guardian, \Neven after his death.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.84,0:14:10.74,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Why did I never put it together?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.47,0:14:14.89,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Servants are summoned from every age.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.52,0:14:21.98,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Heroic Spirits can be summoned from the \Npast, present, or even the distant future.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.82,0:14:25.32,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing says a Servant couldn't be summoned
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.32,0:14:29.01,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,into the time when he lived, \Nto the city in which he once lived.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.95,0:14:32.42,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That thought frustrates me so much.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.42,0:14:34.52,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Because neither one will be saved.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.50,0:14:37.71,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Not the one looking at his past self,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.71,0:14:39.60,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,or the one looking at his future self.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.25,0:14:44.42,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,All I can do is mourn what's become of him.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.84,0:14:49.39,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I already know how it will end for that big fool
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.39,0:14:51.66,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,who tries to live for others.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.39,0:14:56.20,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,He voluntarily sacrificed his afterlife.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.20,0:14:58.90,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If he could keep saving people, even after death,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.90,0:15:01.31,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,he could ask no more.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.67,0:15:04.75,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Because of his powerlessness, \Nhe failed to save people in life.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.75,0:15:08.88,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So, believing that he could avert \Nany tragedy as a Heroic Spirit,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.88,0:15:12.30,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,he sold the peace he would have found in death.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.87,0:15:18.07,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,He believed with all his heart that he could \Nsave tens of thousands more lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.76,0:15:21.84,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But even that hope was betrayed.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.59,0:15:25.94,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Only one thing can be said about him.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.94,0:15:29.38,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That he has been constantly betrayed \Nby everything around him.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.51,0:15:32.35,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And at the very, very end,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.35,0:15:35.28,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,he was betrayed even by the one \Nideal in which he believed.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.57,0:15:51.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What are you trying to pull, Archer?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.16,0:15:59.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Even if I weren't here, Shirou would \Nhave come on his own.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.46,0:16:02.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You should know that better than anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.67,0:16:04.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I suppose you're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.39,0:16:07.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But it would be inconvenient to leave you there.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.01,0:16:09.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.13,0:16:12.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Then you intend to kill Shirou, \Nno matter what, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.72,0:16:17.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, that naïve boy should be \Nput down before it's too late.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.73,0:16:22.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I don't need you to tell me that Shirou is naïve.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.52,0:16:29.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Even so, I think his naïveté is sweet.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.57,0:16:31.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,He ought to stay that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.92,0:16:34.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's good to have a person like that around.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.58,0:16:38.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But what about you?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.50,0:16:40.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,After all you've done,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.04,0:16:43.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,have you decided that waving self-centered \Nidealism in people's faces is wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.29,0:16:47.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Time and time again, you fought for others,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.38,0:16:49.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and time and time again, you were betrayed.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.76,0:16:52.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Time and time again, you were forced \Nto clean up other people's messes.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.22,0:16:54.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Is that...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.30,0:16:57.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Are you saying that's why you \Ngot fed up with humanity,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.66,0:16:58.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Archer?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.81,0:17:06.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,"My body is made of swords."
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.40,0:17:11.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,After you became a Heroic Spirit, that's the \Nincantation you were given, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.53,0:17:14.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's twisted.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.17,0:17:16.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's too much, even as a curse.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.20,0:17:22.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I can't agree with one single thing about your life.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.37,0:17:24.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Not your messed-up way of living,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.50,0:17:27.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,or the people around you who \Ndidn't set you straight.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.46,0:17:29.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I don't even know what to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.09,0:17:32.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I can't agree with it...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.97,0:17:39.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What a surprise, Tohsaka!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.31,0:17:43.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I was skeptical, but here you are, \Nexactly as advertised.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.90,0:17:47.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Shinji?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.27,0:17:48.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Visitors?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.76,0:17:51.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I came here because I thought \Nwe wouldn't be disturbed.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.23,0:17:52.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, now...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.44,0:17:55.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No funny business, Archer.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.36,0:17:57.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not interested in you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.08,0:18:03.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I should warn you, you're no match for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.54,0:18:09.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You're scared, aren't you, Archer?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.29,0:18:13.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That guy's a Servant who dispatched \NBerserker without breaking a sweat.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.61,0:18:16.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I don't blame you for being scared of—
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.00,0:18:18.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You want Rin, Matou Shinji?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.64,0:18:21.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Of course I do.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.93,0:18:24.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Then wait until my business is done.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.77,0:18:27.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Once I've finished Emiya Shirou, she's all yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.23,0:18:32.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If you won't agree, I'll eliminate \Nboth you and your Servant.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.65,0:18:37.67,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Hold on, Gilgamesh.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.67,0:18:40.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's fine. He says he'll give her \Nto us, so let's go along.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.33,0:18:46.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We'll keep Tohsaka safe until \Nhe's dealt with Emiya, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.21,0:18:47.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Which means...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.83,0:18:49.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,She's already as good as mine, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.92,0:18:52.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So I can do anything I want to her, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.25,0:18:57.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,My agreement with Emiya Shirou was \Nthat she'd remain unharmed.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.22,0:18:59.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But that expires at dawn.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.72,0:19:03.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Once the deadline has passed, do as you will.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.23,0:19:10.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Did you hear that, Tohsaka?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.27,0:19:14.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Your Servant sold out his Master!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.11,0:19:20.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Faker.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.42,0:19:35.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You're awake?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.13,0:19:37.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Shirou?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.26,0:19:41.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, the fatigue's gone, \Nand so is my headache.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.36,0:19:44.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,My mana is still pretty depleted,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.81,0:19:47.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,but it seems my Magic Circuits weren't burned out.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.02,0:19:51.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Shirou...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.60,0:19:53.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Rin is my Master.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.86,0:19:56.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Rescuing her is my duty.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.96,0:19:59.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I will stop Archer, so you—
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.57,0:20:00.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's backwards, Saber.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.46,0:20:03.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'll handle the fight with Archer.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.62,0:20:05.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You cannot, Shirou.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.91,0:20:07.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Archer is your...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.58,0:20:08.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.97,0:20:13.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I've probably known who he is \Nsince the moment I met him.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.34,0:20:17.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,All the more reason why I can't \Nlet him get away with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.40,0:20:21.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I have to be the one to settle things with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.89,0:20:25.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Please... I'll fight Archer.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.10,0:20:29.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,When we fight, I want you to stay out \Nof it, no matter what happens.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.52,0:20:35.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If that is your wish, I shall abide by it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.03,0:20:39.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I swore that my body would be your shield.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.70,0:20:43.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Until it is over, I shall simply observe.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.08,0:20:47.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks, Saber.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.50,0:20:57.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm surprised you don't have better things to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.46,0:21:00.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I've changed my mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.17,0:21:03.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The little lady's in trouble, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.57,0:21:06.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So let me tag along a bit longer.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.18,0:21:08.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It would keep me up at night.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.39,0:21:14.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What manner of spell did you and Rin \Nuse to bring him over to your side?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.46,0:23:00.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Ryuudou Temple, Miyama. \NFifty-three unconscious.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.59,0:23:01.75,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,All male.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.21,0:23:04.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Low blood pressure, labored breathing.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.46,0:23:06.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Same symptoms as those other coma cases.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.99,0:23:11.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Send thirty-one to New Fuyuki's general \Nhospital, fifteen to the central hospital,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.60,0:23:14.49,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and the rest to the community hospital.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.69,0:23:29.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Wasn't it my Master's credo to never reveal herself?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.82,0:23:31.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,There can't be two of those pendants.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.83,0:23:34.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Why do your own ideals reject you?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.62,0:23:36.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm leaving this fight before you.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.14,0:23:39.98,Next,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(486,1)}Next Time \NIdealism's End (The Answer)
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.33,0:23:38.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,In any event, you have no future.
